Package data

Class ManagerCSV

java.lang.Object
data.ManagerCSV
public class ManagerCSV extends Object
The ManagerCSV class represents a manager for the CSV files to store the data of those files. This manager will interpret the csv files and convert them into ArrayList<String> following the protocols established in the other managers and in the classes that it is involved in.

ManagerCSV can read csv files that contains items and ratings. To interpret the CSV files we will use OpenCSV a open-source library that it is used to read CSV files.

Version:
v1.0
Author:
Daniel García Estévez

    • readReviews

      private ArrayList<String> readReviews(com.opencsv.CSVReader reader, ArrayList<Integer> pos_col) throws IOException, com.opencsv.exceptions.CsvValidationException
      readReviews() is a function that reads in "reader" the Reviews and returns it. We build the ArrayList<String> following the protocol specify in Review. We use "pos_col" to identifie were are the attributes of a Review object as we have to know for exemple in which column is the id of the user.
      Parameters:
      reader - The CSVReader that allows us to read teh CSV file.
      pos_col - Pos_col works in the following way:
      • The first position of pos_col tell us where is the id of the user.
      • The second position of pos_col tell us where is the id of the item.
      • The third position of pos_col tell us where is the value of the rating.
      • The values of each position can be 0, 1 or 2. For exemple if it is 2, that means it is the third column.
      Returns:
      Returns a set of Reviews represented as a set of strings.
      Throws:
      IOException
      com.opencsv.exceptions.CsvValidationException
